parameters:
True to his words, Zuuteruka was relentless. He relentlessly
defiled me.

Sometimes gently and carefully... and sometimes violently,
as if to ravage me.
One day... and then another day.

Day after day, until the promised day arrived... all day
long... I was continuously defiled by a man I hated to the
point of madness.

\N<Rame>I used to play here a lot with little Riia-chan when we were
younger. That's why I thought it would be nice to... do it
here.
\N<Segi>Nice to... what? What are you talking about?

Even so, I couldn't ignore the message from my mother... I
found myself drawn to this abandoned house in the suburbs as
specified in the letter.

Of course, there's a high possibility of it being some sort
of trap. But I thought it best to do this rather than expose
Lord Yuia to danger...

\N<Boy 2>Hey, are you listening? It's dangerous because this building
is old, we've been told not to play here, right?
\N<Boy 1>It's fine, just for a little bit.
\N<Boy 2>I don't care, I'm going home first, okay?

\N<Boy 1>Hmph, you're such a scaredy-cat for being afraid of getting
scolded.
\N<Boy 1>What's that...? I hear something. Is someone there...?

\N<Man's Voice>Hehehe... Come on, lift your ass higher. It feels better
when it goes in deeper, right?

\N<Man's Voice>Yeah, that's right, good girl. How about it? Feels better
than before, doesn't it? Hehehe.

\N<Man's Voice>Hehehe... You're really hopeless. This is really the last
time, right? We really need to get back to the main troop
soon.

\N<Man's Voice>You too, right? If we're any later, we'll start raising
suspicions, won't we?
